{
  "uuid": "d7c5dc5a49865dbd4c89d584f3263302",
  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Sales Manager (Maritime ERP)",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Identify and develop new business opportunities for a maritime ERP solution, with a strong focus on <strong>shipping accounting and financial modules</strong></p></li><li><p>Build and manage a robust sales pipeline by engaging shipowners, operators, and maritime service providers</p></li><li><p>Drive the full sales cycle from lead generation and product demonstrations to contract negotiation and closing</p></li><li><p>Achieve assigned sales targets through effective prospecting, solution selling, and account development</p></li><li><p>Develop trusted relationships with clients by understanding their accounting workflows, reporting needs, and compliance requirements</p></li><li><p>Collaborate closely with Product, Implementation, Customer Success, and Support teams to ensure smooth onboarding and long-term customer satisfaction</p></li><li><p>Respond promptly to client enquiries and provide professional pre-sales support</p></li><li><p>Monitor market trends, competitor offerings, and customer feedback to refine sales strategies</p></li><li><p>Maintain accurate CRM records, sales reports, and forecasts</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Minimum 2 years of B2B sales experience, preferably within <strong>maritime software, ERP, or shipping-related solutions.</strong></p></li><li><p>Strong interest or background in <strong>shipping accounting, vessel operations, or maritime finance</strong></p></li><li><p>Bachelor’s degree in Business, Finance, Accounting, or a related discipline (or equivalent experience)</p></li><li><p>Comfortable working independently in a regional or international sales role</p></li><li><p>Strong communication, presentation, and negotiation skills, including conducting product demos</p></li><li><p>Results-driven, proactive, and able to manage a structured sales pipeline</p></li><li><p>Analytical mindset with the ability to translate client needs into ERP solutions</p></li><li><p>Excellent planning, time management, and organizational skills</p></li><li><p>Proficient in spoken and written English; additional languages are an advantage</p></li></ul>",
